text: Poticaw Bayou is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to the West Pascagoula River. Poticaw is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "double". Variant names are "Bayou Portico", "Portico Bayo", "Portigo Bayou". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Jackson County, Mississippi
title: Poticaw Bayou
